## Description
How can I add RadioGroup in the same line with another element. By default the RadioGroup breaks in a new line.

## Solution

The RadioGroup adds an `<ul>` which is a block-level element. It will always start on a new line and take up the full width of the page.

Set a [custom CSS Class]({%slug radiogroup-overview%}#features) to separate the specific RadioGroup. Use CSS to override the default `display: flex` of the `ul` to `inline-flex`. Optional, set `vertical-align` to `middle` to have it lined up next to other elements. 

>caption RadioGroup with description and options 

````CSHTML
<strong>How to get in touch?</strong>

<TelerikRadioGroup Data="@scaleModes" 
                   Value="@selectedScaleMode" 
                   Layout="RadioGroupLayout.Horizontal"
                   Class="inline-radiogroup">
</TelerikRadioGroup>

<style>
   .inline-radiogroup.k-list-horizontal{
        display: inline-flex;
        vertical-align: middle; 
    }
</style>

@code{
    List<string> scaleModes { get; set; } = new List<string> { "Phone (SMS)", "E-mail", "None" };

    string selectedScaleMode { get; set; } = "Fixed";
}
````
